ConfEdit (C) 2011 Kantist
=========================


Help message
------------
usage: confedit [-h] [--conf [CONFIG_PATH]] FILE [TOOL]

ConfEdit

positional arguments:
  FILE                  file to edit
  TOOL                  tool to use

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --conf [CONFIG_PATH]  path to configuration file


Configuration sample
--------------------
[TOOLS]
vim
nano
geany
somevar=sometool -arg1 --arg2

[PATHS]
HOME=/home/myname

[FILES]
xinit=$HOME/.xinitrc
i3=$HOME/.i3/config with vim
httpd=/etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf with $somevar


Sample of usage
---------------
[jure@Kant ~]$ confedit xinit haha
> Error running haha /home/jure/.xinitrc:
No such file or directory: 'haha'
[jure@Kant ~]$ confedit xinit
> Edited /home/jure/.xinitrc with vim.
[jure@Kant ~]$ confedit xinit ask
   1) vim
   2) nano
   3) geany
> Choose tool or type a command (default=1): 3
> Edited /home/jure/.xinitrc with geany.
[jure@Kant ~]$ confedit xinit ask
   1) vim
   2) nano
   3) geany
> Choose tool or type a command (default=1): nano -x
> Edited /home/jure/.xinitrc with nano -x.
[jure@Kant ~]$ confedit xinit nano
> Edited /home/jure/.xinitrc with nano.
[jure@Kant ~]$

Recommendedation: create alias for confedit (e.g. "conf" or "edit")
